In ARM, there are two models: ARM state and Thumb state.
In Thumb state, PC points to the one after the next instruction, when current inst. is executed.
In ARM state, PC points to the next instruction.
Read the bx instruction manual, it explains why there is "add r6, pc, #1" and "bx r6".

0x00008ce4 + (0x00008d08 + 4) + 0x00008d80 = 108400
